## Context
Spec writer review: "The ID is the initials of the slug words" is
underspecified:
- What delimiter? (hyphens, but not stated)
- What about single-character IDs? (collision-prone)
- Numeric slug parts? (r2-fix → rf? r2?)
- Is the ID re-derived or immutable after creation?

The parser uses filename prefix (split on first hyphen), not
re-derivation. The spec should document this.

## Actions
1. Add explicit derivation rule: "Split slug on hyphens, take
   first letter of each part. Example: auth-flow-gates → afg"
2. Note that single-character slugs should be avoided
3. State that numeric suffixes for collision (afg2) start at 2
4. Clarify: ID is set once at creation, filename is canonical

## Exit criteria
- A reader can derive any ID from any slug unambiguously
- Edge cases are documented
